-- SolarWorld CEO says U.S. business very good in fourth quarter
-- 
-- Wed Dec 12, 2012 5:15am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/12/us-solarworld-ceo-idUSBRE8BB0H020121212

 

 DUESSELDORF, Germany  (Reuters) - German solar company SolarWorld ( SWVG.DE ) saw very good business in the United States so far in the fourth quarter, Chief Executive Frank Asbeck told Reuters on Wednesday. 
 Asbeck also added that a strategic partnership was one of many options for the group, which had posted a 300 million euro ($389.97 million) net loss for the first nine months of 2012. (Reporting by Anneli Palmen; Writing by  Christoph Steitz )